			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Basically, heres how it works. Its a bit complicated, but once you have it, it will be your favorite AA of all time.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">/Pet Focus</span>
<br />

<br />
Pet Focus is a sort of toggle. You do /pet focus to turn it on, and /pet focus again to turn it off.
<br />

<br />
Under /pet focus, the pet behaves a little differently than you're used to. 
<br />

<br />
When the pet is not attacking, it behaves exactly the same as normal. It will attack mobs that attack you, unless you /pet hold. However, when it is attacking, thats when things are different.
<br />

<br />
Once under /pet focus, the pet will attack mobs when you tell it to, no matter what. It will automatically switch targets whenever you /pet attack, no matter how much hate is built up on your pet, and no matter how low health the pet's current target is.
<br />

<br />
For example, suppose you're fighting a Froglok Krup Knight and a Pox Scarab in Sebilis. Normally you would /pet attack and the pet would attack whichever is at the top of the hate list (and hopefully hold aggro over you). If for whatever reason one mob doesn't attack the pet and instead attacks you, you have to use /pet back off and/or /pet hold to get your pet to attack the other mob. As any experienced mage will tell you, this can be quite a hassle when you have multiple mobs fighting you.
<br />

<br />
Under /pet focus, if you /pet attack the Froglok, the pet will attack the Froglok. It will not attack the Scarab until the Froglok dies, no matter how much damage or hate is built up by the scarab. If you tell the pet to attack the Scarab before the Froglok dies, the pet will stop attacking the Froglok and will attack the Scarab instead.
<br />

<br />
When you turn off /pet focus, the pet resorts to its hate list, and will attack whatever is at the top of the hate list at the time. If you turn on /pet focus while the pet is fighting a mob, it will treat it as if you /pet attack.
<br />

<br />
It will take some getting used to, but once you get the hang of it, it will become your favorite AA. This is definitely a must have AA.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">/pet no cast</span>
<br />

<br />
Works exactly like you think it does. You /pet no cast, and it causes your pet not to use its special abilities (Air Elemental Strike, Water Elemental Strike). Unfortunately when I tested it, it didn't cause the fire pet to not cast useless spells :(
<br />

<br />
This ability will mostly be useful for Earth pets and Water pets. Earth pet for soloing or grouping where root is undesired, and Water for kite groups.</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Guest on Tue Sep 14, 2004 7:06 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
