				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This sure is a comfortable AA, but it does remove the needs for tactics in a few areas of playing a mage where you still need some skill - getting the pet to tank all mobs and getting enough aggro on them.
<br />

<br />
You know when the pet is tanking several mobs, you have other people around and they overaggro on one of them? These people would be tanking or kiting until the mob is dead, letting them learn to study what mob the pet is actually damaging. A memory gone now.
<br />

<br />
Or the tricky pulls in PoSky where it was a great challenge getting your pet to tank the mobs you pulled. They're all casters, so they would often seem to be on the pet, but when they decide to melee, you find that your pet hasn't hit them once, so they head for you, and it would almost be impossible for the pet to regain control unless you got lucky in your kiting.
<br />

<br />
I like that it's a boost in mage power, but it's depressing that it's something that favors the unskilled mage more than the skilled one, as if playing a mage these days wasn't simple and repetitive enough. Having to do a bit of CC through getting the pet to hit all mobs was an interesting matter.
<br />

<br />
I'm guessing the scenario I'll be needing this the most on is when you've got a cleric mob in camp on the pet - it will cast spells mainly and will have less aggro than the other mobs, so before /pet focus you weren't able to get the pet to focus on that mob for more than a moment. Now I will be able to burn down cleric mobs without tanking them myself through overaggro.
<br />

<br />
Speaking of pet changes. I would like to be able to issue pet commands while casting spells, without having to use that primitive tool called the mouse. Then I might actually be using my pet on trash mobs that enrage. It's quite boring to not be able to put the pet on hold just before enrage, and still be able to nuke.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597626">Enharjaren Fenrirsbane</a>  - retired, please don't laugh at my obsolete gear.
<br />
Arch Overseers
<br />
Bristlebane
<br />

<br />
Fruktan - Tauren shaman on Test 1
<br />

<br />
